Server Side Public License (SSPL)

Use of the software: The SSPL permits individuals and organizations to use the software for any purpose, including commercial purposes.

Distribution: If you distribute the software, you must make the source code available under the same license terms. This includes offering the source code to any users interacting with the software over a network.

Network use: Any organization using the software as part of a service provided to others must make the source code available for that service.

Cloud service providers: If you provide the software as a service, you must make the source code of the entire service available under the SSPL.

Modifications: Any modifications made to the software must be released under the SSPL.

Patent grant: Contributors grant users a patent license to any patent claims they hold covering the software.

No trademark rights: The license does not grant trademark rights.
